App-CMAM

The cacm script allows you to watch a specific directory and commit any
changes detected to a Git repository.

To use just do:

    cacm --repo path_to_git_repo --watch directory_to_watch



INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc App::CMAM

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=App-CMAM

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/App-CMAM

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/App-CMAM

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/App-CMAM


